Interface ImmutableProperties<VALUE>

  • Type Parameters:
    VALUE - Tye type of property value, typically Object.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,VALUE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashTreePProperties, SimplisticImmutableProperties

    public interface ImmutableProperties<VALUE>
extends java.util.Map<java.lang.String,VALUE>
    ImmutableProperties is an immutable map with keys that are strings, but with the addition of subMap and sortedKeySet methods.
